@model eTrener.Models.WHRViewModel

@{
    ViewBag.Title = "WHR";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}


<link href="~/Styles/Letter.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"/>
<div class="paper">
    <p class="paper">
        The WHR calculator is a calculator that allows you to accurately determine the type of silhouette and possibly the type of overweight (abdomen or thigh). So you can more accurately develop a DietView for your individual needs.

        To calculate the WHR value, you must first measure waist circumference and hips with a measuring tape. You need to do it as accurately as possible to make the calculations as close to the truth as possible. The type of silhouette and type of overweight is crucial for preparing your DietView.

        The silhouette is divided into two types and represents the WHR.
        <br/><br />
        The index factor of 0.8 or higher in females and 1.0 or higher in males is the apple type.
        <br/>
        The index factor of 0.8 or lower in women and 1.0 or lower in men is the pear type.
        <br/><br />
        The closest to ideal proportions are those with a WHR of 0.7 in women and 1.0 in men.
        <br /><br />
        Preparing the perfect DietView will be much easier knowing the WHR value. So do not treat him as a witch.
    </p>

    <div class="letter">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="box box-primary">

                    @using (Html.BeginForm("WHR", "Calculators", FormMethod.Post, new {role = "form"}))
                    {
                        <div class="box-body">
                            <div class="form-group">
                                @Html.Label("Hip circumference [cm]", new {@class = "col-md-6 control-label"})
                                <div class="col-md-10">
                                    @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.HipCircumference, new {@class = "form-control"})
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="form-group">
                                @Html.Label("Waist circumference [cm]", new {@class = "col-md-6 control-label"})
                                <div class="col-md-10">
                                    @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.WaistCircumference, new {@class = "form-control"})
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="form-group">
                                @Html.LabelFor(m => m.Sex, new {@class = "col-md-4 control-label"})
                                <div class="col-md-10">
                                    @Html.DropDownListFor(m => m.Sex,
                                        new List<SelectListItem>
                                        {
                                            new SelectListItem {Value = "Male", Text = "Male"},
                                            new SelectListItem {Value = "Female", Text = "Female"}
                                        },
                                        new
                                        {
                                            size = "1",
                                            style = "width: 140px"
                                        })
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="box-body">
                                <div class="form-group">
                                    <div class="col-md-12">
                                        @ViewBag.whr <br/>
                                        @ViewBag.result


                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="form-group">
                                <div class="col-md-offset-2 col-md-10">
                                    <br/>
                                    <input type="submit" value="Calculate" class="btn btn-default"/>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    }
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>